&lt;h1 id="groups-never-admit-failure"&gt;Groups Never Admit Failure&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dec 8 2021&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You get a schism instead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Naval:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Groups never admit failure. A group would rather keep living in the mythology of &amp;ldquo;we were repressed&amp;rdquo; than ever admit failure. Individuals are the only ones who admit failure. Even individuals don&amp;rsquo;t like to admit failure, but eventually, they can be forced to.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Accountability Means Letting People Criticize You</title><link>https://linguista.cn/person/naval/orig/accountability-means-letting-people-criticize-you/</link><pubDate>Fri, 21 Jun 2019 18:51:15 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/person/naval/orig/accountability-means-letting-people-criticize-you/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/person/naval/zh/accountability-means-letting-people-criticize-you.zh/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
