&lt;h1 id="theres-no-actual-skill-called-business"&gt;There&amp;rsquo;s No Actual Skill Called &amp;ldquo;Business&amp;rdquo;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apr 8 2019&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3 id="avoid-business-schools-and-magazines"&gt;Avoid business schools and magazines&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Naval:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
In that sense, business to me is bottom of the barrel. There&amp;rsquo;s no actual skill called business, it&amp;rsquo;s too generic. It&amp;rsquo;s like a skill called &amp;ldquo;relating.&amp;rdquo; Like &amp;ldquo;relating to humans.&amp;rdquo; That&amp;rsquo;s not a skill, it&amp;rsquo;s too broad.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Use the wastebasket</title><link>https://linguista.cn/person/terencetao/career-advice/orig/use-the-wastebasket/</link><pubDate>Sun, 06 May 2007 19:05:14 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/person/terencetao/career-advice/orig/use-the-wastebasket/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/person/terencetao/career-advice/zh/use-the-wastebasket.zh/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;
